Chicken in a Fried Onion Sauce (Murgh Resedar)
?

1 1/4 - 1 1/2 lbs chicken
2 medium onions
3/4" cube of fresh ginger
3 garlic cloves
4 tbsp vegetable oil
1/2 tbs coriander seeds
1/2 tbs cumin seeds
1/4 tsp ground turmeric
1/8 tsp cayenne pepper
2 or more tbsp plan yogurt
1 1/4 cup water
1 tomato (peeled)
1 tsp salt
1/4 tsp garam masala
1/2 tbsp finely chopped parsley

Skin chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.  Chop one onion coarsley.  Cut the other onion into thin slices.  Put coarsley chopped onion, ginger and garlic into a food processor and blending until paste is made.  Heat oil in large wide pot over medium heat.  Put in sliced onions, fry until browned.  Remove onions with a slotted spoon, keep as much of the oil in the pot as possible.  Squeeze excess oil from onion.  Put onions aside.  Put paste in pot with oil, until browned (3-4 minutes).  Put in coriander, cumin, turmeric and cayenne.  Put in 1 tbsp of the yogurt, stir for 30 seconds until incorporated in with sauce.  Do another tbsp this way.  Put in chicken pieces, stir.  Add water, tomatoes, salt.  Stir, bring to a boil.  Cover, set heat to low, simmer for 20 minutes.  Sprinkle garam masala, cook for 7 minutes.  Add parsley and serve.
